name: Trixy Dracul
description:
I´ve made this textual inversion, the first one i believe is "good"! it´s based on some images from instagram from the influencer @draculangelica as one of her characters "trixy treats"! It´s a halloween themed character and she´s super sexy :D

here you can find some pictures of her:

https://www.google.com/search?q=trixy+treats&client=opera-gx&hs=pyh&sxsrf=AJOqlzUM_Ef676zIFMBe4l58ZB-oPnFEIg:1675599031973&source=lnms&tbm=isch&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj7wNjorP78AhUSX_EDHTV7CH0Q_AUoAXoECAEQAw&biw=1879&bih=931&dpr=1

-> important <-

i figured out, that adding "room, no person, empty room, architectural" prevents the model to generate just some room with the same color scheme :D

-> important <-

the sample grids have been made with different models available here on civitai, like protogenX53, eldrethsOG4060 and others, for the model to work, just put "trixy_dracul" in your prompt, found it to best work at the beginning! adding ((((beautiful face)))) ((perfect face)) seemed to give better results, without there was some face distortion ...

the training images where full/upper body shots and only the background was changed to be different on all images, so the whole look would somehow be included in the model

the facial makeup is a bit different, SD produces sometimes a bit strange stuff here, but it´s okay i think :D

enjoy

modelVersions.name: V3.0
modelVersions.description:
newest Version, with 3000 steps and much more Vectors per Token (16) to increase detail, second change is, i haven´t removed the background on the source images here, which adds to the overall thing, as there is some sort of carousel as background in the original images :D

third improvement, the facial makeup and such come out much better on this one compared the source images :D
